ch weights instantly, perfect for floor press progressions.<br>Dial from 11 to 66 lbs in seconds; no fumbling, no excuses, just reps.</span></p><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-59_"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-60_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-d4471f69-931d-479c-ac9c-8fb7264f4633"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>$412.79</strong></span></p><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-63_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8fb7264f-4633-47e7-a1b7-d43a7ce9175f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><s>$499.99</s></span></p></div><a href="/products/66lbs" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button2" class="sc-emIqIH hFkfQE pf-66_">Grab Yours — Sale Ends Soon</a></div></div></div></section><div data-section-id="pf-f6d5" data-pf-type="GlobalSection" id="da2abed1-3eba-4f9d-88df-171218c2fe36" class="pf-68_" store="[object Object]">{% capture content %}{% include 'pf-da2abed1' %}{% endcapture %}
            {% if content contains "Liquid error" %}
            {% else %}
            {% render 'pf-da2abed1' %}
            {% endif %}</div><section data-section-id="pf-059d" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-69_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-70_"><strong>Exercise 2: Floor Flyes</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-3a5f" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-72_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="Floor Flyes.gif__PID:9425344a-6813-4c4f-a5f3-28f06350b70f" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Floor_Flyes.gif?v=1764313986&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-73_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-71ce" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-74_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-75_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4f551671-cef9-44aa-8482-1a3860eaec49"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>Floor flyes are similar to the bench version, except that you are limited in your downward movement. That is actually a good thing. Taking your arms lower than the level of your torso is problematic for the shoulder joint. So, the floor actually serves as a built-in safety barrier.<br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br></strong><br>1 - Place a pair&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href="/products/66-lbs-adjustable-weight-dumbbell-set-dt1166" target="_self"><strong><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);"></span></strong></a><a href="/collections/adjustable-dumbbells" target="_self"><strong><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);"></span></strong></a><a href="/collections/adjustable-dumbbells" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);"><u><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);"><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);">d</span></span><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);"><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);">umbbell</span></span><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);"><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);">s</span></span></u></span></a><a href="/collections/adjustable-dumbbells" target="_self"><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);"></span> </a><a href="/collections/adjustable-dumbbells" target="_self"></a>on the floor and sit behind them with your knees bent.<br><br>2 -&nbsp;Grab the dumbbells and roll back to lie flat on your back with the weights above your chest at arm’s length.<br><br>3 -&nbsp;Face your palms together and touch the dumbbells to each other.<br><br>4 -&nbsp;Bend your elbows slightly and keep your arms locked in that position.<br><br>5 -&nbsp;<strong>Pivot from the shoulder as you bring your arms out and slowly down</strong> to touch your elbows to the floor.<br><br>6 -&nbsp;Reverse the action to return to the start position. The only movement should come through the shoulder joint.<br><br>Sets &amp; Reps: 3 sets | 12–15 reps | Rest: 60 seconds<br>Tip: Use a lighter weight than the floor press — this is an isolation exercise. Focus on the stretch and squeeze, not the load.<br></span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-7151" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-78_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-79_"><strong>Exercise 3: Bridge DB Chest Press</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-5d21" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-81_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="Bridge DB Chest Press.gif__PID:97ba93aa-c01f-4cd0-973b-6071e8cf2847" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Bridge_DB_Chest_Press.gif?v=1767162196&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-82_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-6718" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-83_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-84_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-35bf9667-18e8-40c6-b4db-4d8b3d338fbd"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>The bridge version of the floor dumbbell chest press will bring your posterior chain into the movement. Your glutes, hamstrings, and erector spinae will get a workout along with your pecs, delts, and triceps. <br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br><br></strong>1 -&nbsp;Place a pair of dumbbells on the floor and sit behind them with your knees bent.<strong><br></strong><br>2 - Grab the&nbsp;<a href="/products/66-lbs-adjustable-weight-dumbbell-set-dt1166" target="_self"><strong><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);"></span></strong><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.48);"><u><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);">dumbbells</span></u><strong></strong></span></a> and roll back to lie flat on your back with the weights above your chest at arm’s length.<br><br>3-&nbsp;Lift your hips into the air as you keep your feet firmly planted on the floor. Maintain this bridge position throughout the exercise, being sure to keep a neutral spine position.<br><br>4 -&nbsp;Face your palms together and touch the dumbbells to each other.<br><br>5 -&nbsp;Pivot from the shoulder as you bring your arms out and slowly down to touch your elbows to the floor.<br><br>6 - Press back to the starting position.<br><br>Sets &amp; Reps: 3 sets | 10–12 reps | Rest: 75 seconds<br>Tip: Keep your hips elevated for the entire set. If your hips drop, lower the weight and focus on holding the bridge position first.<br></span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-cb6d" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-87_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-88_"><strong>Exercise 4:DB Floor Pull-Over</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-0ca2" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-90_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="DB Floor PullOver.gif__PID:1338b73f-3e2b-4a86-a274-b0f7a220a8d0" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Floor_PullOver.gif?v=1764064000&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-91_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-0d9e" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-92_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-93_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-aad8380d-9e8a-4980-94bf-05b99a463d10"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>The floor pullover will give your pecs a great stretch. The old belief that it will expand your ribcage has been debunked but it's still a decent chest move. <br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br><br>1 -&nbsp;</strong>Lie on the floor with your knees bent and a single dumbbell held above your chest at arm’s length in both hands by one end with a cupped grip.<strong><br></strong><br>2 - Breathe out as pivot from the shoulder to bring the weight back and down behind your head. Go all the way back until the dumbbell touches the floor. Do not bend the elbows.<br><br>3-&nbsp;Breathe in as you return to the start position.<br><br>Sets &amp; Reps: 3 sets | 12–15 reps | Rest: 60 seconds<br>Tip: Keep your lower back pressed to the floor throughout. Do not arch up as the dumbbell passes overhead.<br></span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-4858" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-96_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-97_"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-98_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-99_">Train Smarter. Pay Less. Start Today.</h2><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-101_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5836bf9f-8782-4cda-bed8-44b00812b0c1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Join AtivaPeople for free and instantly unlock 10% off</span></p><a href="https://www.ativafit.com/pages/ativapeople-rewards-program" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button2" class="sc-emIqIH hFkfQE pf-104_">Claim 10% Off Now — It's Free</a></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-106_"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-107_"><img alt="_鍥惧眰_1.png__PID:34c0ffda-071a-4f0f-a205-36ee9832fa9e" src="https://cd