Guidance</span></p></div></div></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-e4c3" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-122_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-123_"><strong>Exercise 5: DB Push-Ups</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-5cdb" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-125_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="DB Push-Ups" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Push-Ups.gif?v=1767162790&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-126_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-b60e" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-127_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-128_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5f2c6db6-0e4c-4e11-abe4-346d5d3694c2"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>The dumbbell push-up is more wrist-friendly than the standard push-up. It also allows you to go a few inches deeper than the standard push-up.  <br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br><br></strong>1 -&nbsp;Get down on the floor in the start position of a push-up with a pair of dumbbells in your hands. If possible, use hexagonal dumbbells as these will sit flat on the floor. Take your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.<strong><br></strong><br>2 - Maintaining a straight line from head to foot, lower down below the level of the dumbbells to fully stretch the pecs.<br><br>3&nbsp;-&nbsp;Push back to the start position.<br><br> Sets &amp; Reps: 3–4 sets | 10–15 reps | Rest: 75 seconds<br>Tip: Lower your body as deep as possible past the level of the dumbbell handles — this extra range of motion is the main advantage over standard push-ups.<br></span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-44de" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-131_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-132_"><strong>Exercise 6: DB Squeeze Press</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-be4a" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-134_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="DB Squeeze Press" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/DB_Squeeze_Press.gif?v=1767162846&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-135_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-12e4" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-136_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-137_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-d41b7512-e409-4876-84dc-1dd824416f91"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>The squeeze press is a combination between an isometric hold and a horizontal adduction move. Do it at the end of your workout for an awesome finishing pump.  <br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br><br></strong>1 -&nbsp;Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and a single dumbbell held in both hands at chest level. Your hands should be clasped together around the ends of the <span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.45);"><strong><a href="/products/66-lbs-adjustable-weight-dumbbell-set-dt1166" target="_self"></a></strong></span><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.45);"><strong><a href="/products/66-lbs-adjustable-weight-dumbbell-set-dt1166" target="_self"></a></strong></span><a href="/collections/adjustable-dumbbells" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);"><u><span style="background-color: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.45);"><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);">dumbbell</span></span> </u></span></a>so that you are holding it horizontally.<strong><br></strong><br>2 - With the dumbbell touching your chest, forcefully squeeze your pecs together.<br><br>3&nbsp;-&nbsp;Press the dumbbell out to full arm extension, maintaining the squeeze as you do so.<br><br>4 -&nbsp;Return to the start position, making sure that the dumbbell does not drop toward the floor as you do so.<br><br>Sets &amp; Reps: 3 sets | 12–15 reps | Rest: 45 seconds<br>Tip: The squeeze is everything in this exercise. If you stop squeezing the dumbbell between your palms, you lose the pec activation completely.<br> </span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-33c8" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-140_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-141_"><strong>Exercise 7: Renegade Push-Ups</strong></h2></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-06c8" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-143_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><img alt="Renegade Rows.gif__PID:2598e2d6-d054-4249-b168-49983dee8279" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Renegade_Rows_2c164db0-d25f-4eb3-969f-9707b58ddcc8.gif?v=1764063948&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.775" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-fscnvs dncZrx pf-144_" store="[object Object]"/></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-00e0" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-145_ pf-container-1"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-146_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-e53f8800-e03c-4013-8243-8e89dd71fe70"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>Why Do It:</strong><br><br>The renegade push-up is a combination move that works the back muscles as well as the chest. The constant switching between lat and pec work will give you an awesome upper body pump.  <br><br><strong>How To Do It:<br><br></strong>1 -&nbsp;Get down on the floor in the start position of a push-up with a pair of dumbbells in your hands. If possible, use hexagonal dumbbells as these will sit flat on the floor. Your hands should be directly under your shoulders.<strong><br></strong><br>2 - <strong>Row the left-hand dumbbell up to your ribcage.</strong><br><br>3&nbsp;-&nbsp;<strong>Perform a push-up.<br><br></strong>4 -&nbsp;Row the right-hand dumbbell up to your ribcage.<br><strong><br></strong>5 -&nbsp;Continue in this alternating manner to complete your rep count.<br><strong><br>This is just one more exercise that you should be doing on <u><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);">chest day</span></u>.<br><br></strong>Sets &amp; Reps: 3 sets | 6–8 reps per side | Rest: 90 seconds<br>Tip: Count each push-up as one rep, not each row. Keep your hips square to the floor when rowing — do not rotate your torso. If you want to train your back on a separate day, check out our <a href="https://www.ativafit.com/blogs/exercise-tips/pull-day-workout-with-dumbbells-at-home" target="_blank"><u><span style="color: rgb(245, 166, 35);">pull day dumbbell workout</span></u></a> for more row variations.<strong><br></strong> </span></p></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-01d1" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-gKlDTn jrBPeP pf-149_ pf-container-1 pf-sm-hide pf-hide"><div class="sc-jRGIGG bMuAgN pf-flex-section"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-150_"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-fYXHKj TqaeK pf-151_"><img alt="Group 25.png__PID:29438d2a-94fd-44ae-8c73-ba96766aa110" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2623/4904/files/Group_25.png?v=1762991593&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.s